SEARCH
Package entities

Class Reservation

java.lang.Object
entities.Reservation
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Reservation extends Object implements Serializable
Represents a reservation made by a subscriber for a parking spot. This class is used both to display upcoming reservations in the client GUI and to send new reservation requests from the client to the server.

  • Constructor Details

    • Reservation

      public Reservation(int reservationId, String subscriberId, String parkingCode, LocalDate entryDate, LocalTime entryTime, LocalDate exitDate, LocalTime exitTime, int parkingSpot)
      Constructs a fully populated Reservation instance. This constructor is typically used when loading existing reservations from the database.
      Parameters:
      reservationId - The unique ID of the reservation.
      subscriberId - The ID of the subscriber who made the reservation.
      parkingCode - The parking code associated with the reservation.
      entryDate - The date the reservation begins.
      entryTime - The time the reservation begins.
      exitDate - The date the reservation ends.
      exitTime - The time the reservation ends.
      parkingSpot - The parking spot number assigned to the reservation.

    • Reservation

      public Reservation(String subscriberId, LocalDate entryDate, LocalTime entryTime)
      Constructs a Reservation for sending a new reservation request from the client to the server, with only subscriber ID and entry time.
      Parameters:
      subscriberId - The ID of the subscriber.
      entryDate - The requested entry date.
      entryTime - The requested entry time.
